<br>
True. I like the symbolism too, but I think the argument that it is necessary to baptism would be like saying, &quot;it is necessary to have wine at a wedding for the marriage to be valid, because at the wedding at Cana there was wine and that best associates us with the Gospel account of weddings&quot; A rediculous argument as you can see.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>&quot;What baptism is,&quot; I interpretted to mean the process... <hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
